<div id="review_2893895607" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2893895607" />
    <a title="Clark" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25204679-clark"><img alt="Clark" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1383238475p2/25204679.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2893895607?book_show_action=true">Jul 12, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Clark" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Clark" href="/user/show/25204679-clark">Clark</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2893895607" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6021871329229823784">I read this book as I have a heritage from the Netherlands, and descend from the original Dutch colonial families on both sides of my family. The book was a fast read. I really wanted to like this book, however it is very It is in a genre I call &apos;History light&apos; where it is just a very basic history book that just tells the reader very basic history without much depth, and honestly Russell Shorto is not that good of a historian. Shorto takes way too many liberties with Adriaen van der Donck, clai</span>
  <span id="freeText6021871329229823784" style="display:none">I read this book as I have a heritage from the Netherlands, and descend from the original Dutch colonial families on both sides of my family. The book was a fast read. I really wanted to like this book, however it is very It is in a genre I call 'History light' where it is just a very basic history book that just tells the reader very basic history without much depth, and honestly Russell Shorto is not that good of a historian. Shorto takes way too many liberties with Adriaen van der Donck, claiming that Adriaen van der Donck 'possibly' did this, or 'might' or 'probably' did something when in actuality there is no real proof of his claims at all. Shorto also tends to go off on way too many tangents, or go off topic about things that have absolutely nothing to do with the subject he wrote about. The book needed to be edited down by about 100 pages.<br /><br />Also the author Shorto is completely incorrect as New Netherland is not forgotten at all, and it was never forgotten. Another negative and very glaring error is how Shorto claims that the Dutch were the first to bring religious freedom or religious tolerance to North America, while completely ignoring both Roger Williams and William Penn. So that is why I gave the book 2 stars instead of 3-5.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6021871329229823784" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


