<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer3222225703288263824">Russell Shorto is the author, most recently, of <u>Revolution Song</u>, a new narrative of the American Revolution, which the New York Times called a &quot;remarkable&quot; achievement and the Chicago Tribune described as &quot;an engaging piece of historical detective work and narrative craft.&quot; He is also the author of <u>The Island at the Center of the World</u>, a national bestseller about the Dutch founding of New York. S</span>
  <span id="freeText3222225703288263824" style="display:none">Russell Shorto is the author, most recently, of <u>Revolution Song</u>, a new narrative of the American Revolution, which the New York Times called a "remarkable" achievement and the Chicago Tribune described as "an engaging piece of historical detective work and narrative craft." He is also the author of <u>The Island at the Center of the World</u>, a national bestseller about the Dutch founding of New York. Shorto is senior scholar at the New Netherland Institute and was formerly the director of the John Adams Institute in Amsterdam. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3222225703288263824" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
